text: Honestly, this looks like it could be good!  The main "issue" I'm seeing is that the animation isn't in the "normal" CGI style (especially the kids, who would normally have eyes literally bigger than their brains in any sort of modern animation style) which IMO could lend a hand to the  characters' "abnormal creep" factor, provided anyone OUTSIDE the family still looks relatively normal so as to give the designs contrast.  My main concern is that the jokes won't land, or won't be in the spirit of the original show, thus making the end product unfaithful if not outright bad.    Specifically regarding the movie being unfaithful: should that be an issue it'd be giving the kids who haven't watched the show previously the wrong impression about The Addams Family, which might turn them off of the original regardless of the quality of this movie.

text: The animation is probably the weakest looking element of the film so far, especially in the scene where spiders crawl out of morticia to make a bridge. The designs are nice, as I really love seeing the old designs from the original animated tv show. But they don't really translate well into 3D animation. The character animation especially feels a little stiff. It's not bad but it's not good either.  What's even weirder is the fact that apparently this is the same animation company that did Sausage Party. In that movie the animation was supposed to look bland because the movie was parodying animated films in general. Here, the studio is adapting a beloved series. While the movie itself doesn't look bad, I just think it deserves to be made by a better studio. Bless them for trying, but I don't think they're really succeeding.

text: Okay, so I've slept on it. I meditated about it. And I've finally decided that I'm okay with this existing. Addam's family is very G rated dark humor that is more or less Dry humor with very little flair.  The movies were sort of a departure with there being a plot (the same plot I might add) and the selling point of the films were the performances. There's some of that in this but this is them just hanging out in their home. The Addam's family is always funny when they contrast to normal people.    The movie won't be them in their house the whole time I imagine. Someone normal will enter the house or the family leaves the house on multiple occasions.    If the movie is average at best it will be a good entry for this particular franchise. The bar isn't really that high.
